<article id="post-450" class="post-450 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-general category-rants">
	<header class="entry-header">
		
		<h2 class="entry-title"><a href="http://geoff.wp/2006/08/a-comment-on-stupidity/" rel="bookmark">A comment on stupidity</a></h2>	</header><!-- .entry-header -->

	
	
	<div class="entry-content">
		<p>When did society become responsible for the stupidity of individuals?<br />
Over the last few years, there&#8217;s been a disturbing trend where corporations (and governments, through the courts) have had to start protecting the stupid. Not the mentally disabled &#8212; the stupid. Seemingly ordinary people that, on the surface, you&#8217;d probably never suspect of being a moron. And yet, these people are the ones who end up affecting the rest of us because they feel they were specifically picked upon and justified in their retribution.<br />
What am I referring to? Cold coffee. Quiet iPods. Notices of the blatantly obvious.<br />
 <a href="http://geoff.wp/2006/08/a-comment-on-stupidity/#more-450" class="more-link">Continue reading<span class="screen-reader-text"> &#8220;A comment on stupidity&#8221;</span></a></p>
	</div><!-- .entry-content -->

	<footer class="entry-footer">
