<article id="post-539" class="post-539 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-general category-rants category-travel tag-around-the-world tag-internet tag-russia">
	<header class="entry-header">
		
		<h2 class="entry-title"><a href="http://geoff.wp/2005/05/the-internyet/" rel="bookmark">The internyet</a></h2>	</header><!-- .entry-header -->

	
	
	<div class="entry-content">
		<p>Okay, just a general bitch about Russia.<br />
Where the hell are all the internet cafes?? Our guides are out of date &#8212; we accept that. But do we have to traipse around every city for an hour looking for the damn things?! I mean, really, people &#8212; Russia is not that backwards, is it? Even the post offices aren&#8217;t consistent. Some have internet, some have internyet.<br />
I can&#8217;t wait to see how hard it is in China&#8230; (we&#8217;re only in Ulaan Baatar in Mongolia, and god help us there)</p>
	</div><!-- .entry-content -->

	<footer class="entry-footer">
